        " «يُلْقِيهَا عَنْهُ إِنْ شَاءَ أَوْ يَدْفِنُهَا فِي اَلْحَصَى."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1068 - Muhammad ibn Muslim asked Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) about a person who is harmed by an animal while he is praying.\nHe (as) replied: \"He should throw it away from him if he wishes, or bury it in the pebbles.\""
        ]
